cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on spoken dialogue interaction with multiple robots and presents a MultiBot testing scenario. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of existing tools for speech recognition and dialogue management, which are AI-related technologies. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of language in the interaction between humans and robots. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper focuses on the interaction between humans and robots through spoken dialogue. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is also relevant as the paper discusses an inter-agent communication protocol for assigning tasks to the appropriate robot.
